<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD7AF2EC98E998DFA3096AB" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" type="key">
<keyStep id="308632FEFFD7AF2EC98E998DFA319621" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD7AF2EC98E998DFA30965B" blockId="2.[151,1437,723,980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<keyLead id="3083896EFFD7AF2EC98E998DFA30965B" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD7AF2EC98E998DFF079797" bold="true" box="[151,170,723,744]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">1.</emphasis>
Temples not prominent; neck region indistinct (e.g., fig. 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD7AF2ECA11998AFC829795" box="[776,815,724,746]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD7AF2ECA2C998AFBB49795" author="Ito, T. &amp; Yoshitomi, H." box="[821,1049,724,746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" pagination="113 - 118" refId="ref5540" refString="Ito, T. &amp; Yoshitomi, H. (2017 a) Four new species of the genus Prostomis (Coleoptera, Prostomidae) from the Oriental Region. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 23, 113 - 118." type="journal article" year="2017">Ito &amp; Yoshitomi 2017a</bibRefCitation>
). Mandibles elongate; incisor edge with many teeth (fig. 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD7AF2EC89899AFFE1F9678" box="[385,434,753,775]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.128" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" unit="in" value="32.0">32 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD7AF2EC8A199AFFDF69678" author="Schawaller, W." box="[440,603,753,775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref6276" refString="Schawaller, W. (1991) Prostomidae (Coleoptera) aus dem Himalaya mit einem beitrag zur larvalmorphologie. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), 461, 1 - 17. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1991">Schawaller 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Jugular processes (anteriorly produced genae) elongate, usually as long as mandibles (fig. 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD7AF2EC8089850FE9B965B" box="[273,310,782,804]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD7AF2EC8229851FDB5965B" author="Ito, T. &amp; Yoshitomi, H." box="[315,536,782,804]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" pagination="113 - 118" refId="ref5540" refString="Ito, T. &amp; Yoshitomi, H. (2017 a) Four new species of the genus Prostomis (Coleoptera, Prostomidae) from the Oriental Region. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 23, 113 - 118." type="journal article" year="2017">Ito &amp; Yoshitomi 2017a</bibRefCitation>
).......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD7AF2ECDC59850FA30965B" authority="Latreille" authorityName="Latreille" box="[1244,1437,782,804]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Prostomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD7AF2ECDC59850FA30965B" bold="true" box="[1244,1437,782,804]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD7AF2ECDC59850FA92965C" bold="true" box="[1244,1343,782,803]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Prostomis</emphasis>
Latreille
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD7AF2EC98E9872FA319621" blockId="2.[151,1437,723,980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<keyLead id="3083896EFFD7AF2EC98E9872FA319621" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD7AF2EC98E9872FF32963E" bold="true" box="[151,159,812,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">-</emphasis>
Temples distinctly projected posterolaterally; neck region distinct (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2ECA739872FC62963E" box="[874,975,812,834]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,260,1430,1456]" captionTargetBox="[179,1399,190,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[179,1409,179,1405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Extant Dryocora spp., deposited in Australian National Insect Collection. A, Dryocora walkeri, dorsal view. B–E, Dryocora howitti. B, Habitus, dorsal view. C, Habitus, ventral view. D, Head, ventral view. E, Head, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm in A–C, 500 μm in D–E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457398/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Figs 1D,E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2ECAC39872FBA2963E" box="[986,1039,812,833]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,260,1723,1749]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-61@4.[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytral apex, dorsal view. D, Pterothorax, ventral view. E, Abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; jp, jugular process; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457408/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">3A,B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2ECD039872FB97963E" box="[1050,1082,812,833]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">7B</figureCitation>
). Mandibles short; incisor edge with 1–2 teeth (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2EC85E9817FE399621" box="[327,404,841,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,260,1430,1456]" captionTargetBox="[179,1399,190,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[179,1409,179,1405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Extant Dryocora spp., deposited in Australian National Insect Collection. A, Dryocora walkeri, dorsal view. B–E, Dryocora howitti. B, Habitus, dorsal view. C, Habitus, ventral view. D, Head, ventral view. E, Head, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm in A–C, 500 μm in D–E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457398/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Figs 1E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2EC8869817FE139621" box="[415,446,841,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,260,1723,1749]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-61@4.[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytral apex, dorsal view. D, Pterothorax, ventral view. E, Abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; jp, jugular process; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457408/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">3D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2EC8D19817FE459621" box="[456,488,841,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">7H</figureCitation>
). Jugular processes shorter (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2ECBEE9817FCEA9621" box="[759,839,841,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,260,1430,1456]" captionTargetBox="[179,1399,190,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[179,1409,179,1405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Extant Dryocora spp., deposited in Australian National Insect Collection. A, Dryocora walkeri, dorsal view. B–E, Dryocora howitti. B, Habitus, dorsal view. C, Habitus, ventral view. D, Head, ventral view. E, Head, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm in A–C, 500 μm in D–E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457398/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Figs 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD7AF2ECA489817FCC29621" box="[849,879,841,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,260,1723,1749]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-61@4.[151,1436,306,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Vetuprostomis angularis Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177907, under widefield fluorescence. A, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. B, Head and prothorax, ventral view. C, Elytral apex, dorsal view. D, Pterothorax, ventral view. E, Abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: an, antenna; el, elytron; jp, jugular process; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus. Scale bars: 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457408/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">3B</figureCitation>
, 
